-- Moody’s German Outlook Hurt by Spain, Italy, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   J e f f   B l a c k
-- 2012-07-25T05:53:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-25/moody-s-german-outlook-hurt-by-spain-italy-handelsblatt-says.html
Moody’s Investors Service lowered
its rating outlook for Germany to negative because of the
possibility that Spain and Italy will need euro-area financial
aid, company analyst  Dietmar Hornung  told  Handelsblatt .  German banks’ holdings of the two nations’ sovereign debt
is a problem for Germany, Handelsblatt cited Hornung as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
